1️⃣ Stored Procedures (Reusable Logic)
Simple Idea

A Stored Procedure is a saved set of SQL statements inside the database

👉 You can call it anytime like a function

Mental Model 🧠
Stored Procedure = SQL function stored in DB
Why We Need It

Without stored procedure ❌:

You write same query again & again

With stored procedure ✅:

Write once, reuse anytime
Example

👉 “Get all CSE students”

Create Procedure
CREATE PROCEDURE get_cse_students()
BEGIN
    SELECT * FROM students WHERE branch='CSE';
END;
Call Procedure
CALL get_cse_students();
Python Connection 🧠
def get_cse_students():
    return [s for s in students if s["branch"] == "CSE"]

👉 Stored Procedure ≈ Python function

With Parameters 🔥
CREATE PROCEDURE get_students_by_branch(IN b VARCHAR(50))
BEGIN
    SELECT * FROM students WHERE branch = b;
END;

Call:

CALL get_students_by_branch('ECE');
Why Stored Procedures Are Powerful

✔ Reusable logic
✔ Faster execution (precompiled)
✔ Secure (hide SQL logic)

Memory Trick 🧠
Stored Procedure = Reusable SQL function
2️⃣ Triggers (Automatic Execution)
Simple Idea

A Trigger runs automatically when an event happens

👉 You don’t call it manually

Mental Model 🧠
Trigger = Automatic reaction
Real-World Example

👉 When a new student is added → log it automatically

Example Table
students
id	name
log_table
message
Create Trigger
CREATE TRIGGER after_student_insert
AFTER INSERT ON students
FOR EACH ROW
BEGIN
    INSERT INTO log_table VALUES ('New student added');
END;
What Happens
INSERT INTO students VALUES (1,'Akshay');

👉 Automatically:

"New student added"

is inserted into log_table

Types of Triggers
Type	When it runs
BEFORE	Before operation
AFTER	After operation
Events
Event	Meaning
INSERT	New data added
UPDATE	Data changed
DELETE	Data removed
Python Connection 🧠
def insert_student(student):
    students.append(student)
    log.append("New student added")

👉 Trigger = automatic function call

Why Triggers Are Useful

✔ Automation
✔ Data auditing
✔ Enforcing rules
✔ Logging changes

Memory Trick 🧠
Trigger = Automatic action on event
🔥 Placement Insight

Very common questions:

Q1: Difference between Stored Procedure and Trigger?
Feature	Stored Procedure	Trigger
Execution	Manual	Automatic
Use	Reusable logic	Event-based action
Q2: Can we pass parameters to trigger?

👉 ❌ No (automatic execution)

Q3: When are triggers used?

👉 Logging, validation, automation

